window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>A Warhammer 40,000 audio drama collection.</p> <p>The Space Wolves are among the mightiest of mankind's defenders, savage and brutal warriors who always fight for what is right, no matter the cost.</p> <p><b>Listen to it because:</b></p> <p>Experience seven sagas of the Space Wolves with a bundle of action-packed audio dramas that showcase the sons of Fenris at their finest!</p> <p>From their unassailable polar stronghold, the Fang, on the frozen death world of Fenris, the Space Wolves cast off into the Sea of Stars seeking out Mankindâ€™s most vicious enemies to defeat in glorious battle. Each Space Wolf is a warrior of legend whose heroic deeds are recorded in epic sagas. </p> <p>This audio drama anthology contains seven tales of the Space Wolves. In these stories, you'll discover the moment the Chapter changed forever, ride across the frozen tundra, experience battles with orks, drukhari and more, witness the infamous Lukas the Trickster at work and see the dynamic between the sons of Russ and their rivals in the Dark Angels. </p> <p>Contents: </p> <p>'Thunder from Fenris' by Nick Kyme.</p> <p>'The Art of Provocation' by Josh Reynolds.</p> <p>'Parting of the Ways' by Chris Wraight.</p> <p>'Iceclaw' by Ben Counter.</p> <p>'Doomseeker' by Nick Kyme.</p> <p>'Deathwolf' by Andy Smillie.</p> <p>'Vox Tenebris' by Robbie MacNiven.</p> <p>Performed by Toby Longworth, John Banks, Jonathan Keeble, Peter Noble, Sean Barrett, Ian Brooker, Ramon Tikaram, Rupert Degas, Steve Conlin, Chris Fairbank, Charlotte Paige, Robin Bowerman, David Timson, Gareth Armstrong.</p>"; 
